<ReportItem port="8081" svc_name="www" protocol="tcp" severity="0" pluginID="10386" pluginName="Web Server No 404 Error Code Check" pluginFamily="Web Servers">
<description>The remote web server is configured such that it does not return &apos;404 Not Found&apos; error codes when a nonexistent file is requested, perhaps returning instead a site map, search page or authentication page.

Nessus has enabled some counter measures for this.  However, they might be insufficient.  If a great number of security holes are produced for this port, they might not all be accurate.</description>
<fname>no404.nasl</fname>
<plugin_modification_date>2022/06/17</plugin_modification_date>
<plugin_name>Web Server No 404 Error Code Check</plugin_name>
<plugin_publication_date>2000/04/28</plugin_publication_date>
<plugin_type>remote</plugin_type>
<risk_factor>None</risk_factor>
<script_version>1.100</script_version>
<solution>n/a</solution>
<synopsis>The remote web server does not return 404 error codes.</synopsis>
<plugin_output>
The following string will be used :
not found</plugin_output>
</ReportItem>
