<ReportItem port="8081" svc_name="www" protocol="tcp" severity="0" pluginID="42822" pluginName="Strict Transport Security (STS) Detection" pluginFamily="Service detection">
<asset_inventory>True</asset_inventory>
<description>The remote web server implements Strict Transport Security (STS).
The goal of STS is to make sure that a user does not accidentally downgrade the security of his or her browser.

All unencrypted HTTP connections are redirected to HTTPS.  The browser is expected to treat all cookies as &apos;secure&apos; and to close the connection in the event of potentially insecure situations.</description>
<fname>sts_detect.nasl</fname>
<plugin_modification_date>2019/11/22</plugin_modification_date>
<plugin_name>Strict Transport Security (STS) Detection</plugin_name>
<plugin_publication_date>2009/11/16</plugin_publication_date>
<plugin_type>remote</plugin_type>
<risk_factor>None</risk_factor>
<script_version>1.7</script_version>
<see_also>http://www.nessus.org/u?2fb3aca6</see_also>
<solution>n/a</solution>
<synopsis>The remote web server implements Strict Transport Security.</synopsis>
<plugin_output>
The STS header line is :

Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains
</plugin_output>
</ReportItem>
